After resting in the Lonely Light castle of the Farwynds, Arya would likely find a new continent while sailing into the Sunset Sea. The condition of Westeros resembles Europe in the age of explorations, as the realm is in a rather stable state after a turbulent period of wars and disasters. Even though Bran did not foresee the discovery of the new world, I still think that the existence of a new continent, east of Asshai and west of Westeros, is possible. Since the Westerosi did not have the motivations to find a new path to Asshai as much as the Europeans wanted to find a new route to Asia, they would focus more on settlement-based colonization instead of exploitation-based colonization. A example of settlement-based colonization in our timeline is the colonies in North America. The thirteen colonies did not posses an abundance of natural resources, thus the English settlers practiced agriculture and developed the land there. As a result, the economic development of North American colonies is much more sustainable. On the other hand, the Latin American colonies were more populated and rich in resources. The Spanish and the Portuguese did not have to develop the land to gain profit. This difference in colonial policy resulted in difference in development levels now. The Westerosi would likely colonize the new continent using the English settler model, building a thriving economy in the west.

At Penn, learning and growth happen outside of the classrooms, too. How will you explore the community at Penn? Consider how this community will help shape your perspective and identity, and how your identity and perspective will help shape this community. (150-200 words)

In Penn, I would like to scale up my current soap business Soapaholic to continue contributing to universal sanitary. By joining the Wharton Undergraduate Entrepreneurship Club, I could collaborate with people filled with business passion and novel ideas. Through discussions with VIP-C, new ideas to improve my business will be ignited, and I could obtain resources to better scale-up Soapaholic. After learning more about entrepreneurship and forming bonds with people through the club, I would like to start up my own club call Pennetration, which aims to reach universal sanitary through the power of business. I could spread my knowledge of making soap to the members and raise the awareness of sanitary necessity for people in need by selling our soaps in and out of the campus. By taking in different perspectives through cooperating with others, I could produce more types of products and accumulate a stronger momentum to penetrate our will to help into the world.
	Furthermore, I would like to join The Daily Pennsylvanian and write for the Under the Button publication because I love to laugh and spread laughters to lighten otherâs days.  By utilizing the interview, observation, and journal writing skills I gained from being the editor in Circular Economy Jr., I would love to explore and portray all the humorous moments in Penn everyday. I look forward to being immersed in Pennâs daily happiness and implementing my editor skills and positive energy to give everyone something to laugh at after a stressful day.
